================================================================================
Bundled WebAssembly module: vendor/e57-wasm
================================================================================

The q3dweb/vendor/e57-wasm crate is built from the following Rust crates and
compiled into the WebAssembly artifact shipped under
vendor/e57-wasm/pkg/e57_wasm_bg.wasm:

- e57 (MIT)
  https://github.com/cry-inc/e57
  A pure Rust library for reading and writing E57 point cloud files.

- wasm-bindgen, js-sys, wasm-bindgen-macro, wasm-bindgen-macro-support,
  wasm-bindgen-shared (MIT OR Apache-2.0)
  https://github.com/rustwasm/wasm-bindgen

- roxmltree (MIT OR Apache-2.0)
  https://github.com/RazrFalcon/roxmltree

- bumpalo, cfg-if, once_cell, proc-macro2, quote, rustversion, syn
  (MIT OR Apache-2.0)

- memchr (Unlicense OR MIT)
  https://github.com/BurntSushi/memchr

- unicode-ident ((MIT OR Apache-2.0) AND Unicode-3.0)
  https://github.com/dtolnay/unicode-ident

================================================================================
External runtime resources (when used)
================================================================================

If the viewer is configured to fetch map tiles from OpenStreetMap, GSI (地理院
タイル), or other tile providers, those resources are subject to the tile
provider's terms of use and require appropriate attribution. Please follow
each provider's guidelines when redistributing or displaying the tiles.
